ABOUT THIS FILE:

This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com.

When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:

summary(cars)

Charts Summary

Chart 1 Descriptive paragraph

We made a scatterplot to analyze the correlation between the overall score and price on booking.com website. However, we omitted some observations that contain missing values. As a result, in this scatterplot, we can detect a positive correlation between the overall score and the price. This result answers one of the research questions we created on the project proposal.

Chart 2 Descriptive paragraph

This is a bar graph that shows the top 15 hotels that got the most reviews from booking.com. However, in our code, there are some issues that there are some hotels who receive a few reviews but are shown in the bar graph. (to be fixed) In this visulization, we want to focus on the hotels thet get most reviews and compared them with more detailed variables such as location, cleanliness, facilities, and more in our future report.
